SUMMARY:Tour of Thomas Hart Benton's Indiana Murals
DESCRIPTION:This tour visitsThe Hall of Murals at IU Auditorium  IU Cinem
 a  Woodburn Hall  About the Indiana Murals:  Thomas Hart Benton was commi
 ssioned to paint murals depicting Indiana history for the Indiana state p
 avilion at the 1933 World's Fair in Chicago. The dramatic 250-foot long m
 ural\, which originally wrapped around the entire exhibition hall at the 
 World's Fair\, depicts the social\, economic\, and cultural history of In
 diana from mound building to the 1930s. After several years of storage fo
 llowing the fair\, the panels were given to Indiana University in 1938\, 
 where they were installed in three locations on the Bloomington campus.&#
 160\;About Your Guide:  Jim Davis is a Senior Lecturer in the Kelley Scho
 ol of Business\, in the department of Management and Entrepreneurship. He
  has been serving as a docent and museum guide at the IU Eskenazi Museum 
 of Art for the past ten years.&#160\; &#160\; &#160\;Know Before You GoTh
 is tour visits three locations on campus. Please let us know if an elevat
 or and wheelchair accessible route will be needed.&#160\;  Plan to arrive
  at least 5 minutes beforehand to check in.For a discounted parking rate 
 for the Indiana Memorial Union parking lot\, visit the Eskenazi Museum of
  Art before or after this tour and ask Guest Services\, at the Informatio
 n Desk on the first floor\, to stamp your parking voucher.
