  Murals at IU Auditorium  </li><li>IU Cinema  </li><li>Woodburn Hall  </l
 i></ul><h4><strong>About the Indiana Murals:</strong></h4><p>  Thomas Har
 t Benton was commissioned to paint murals depicting Indiana history for t
 he Indiana state pavilion at the 1933 World's Fair in Chicago. The dramat
 ic 250-foot long mural\, which originally wrapped around the entire exhib
 ition hall at the World's Fair\, depicts the social\, economic\, and cult
 ural history of Indiana from mound building to the 1930s. After several y
 ears of storage following the fair\, the panels were given to Indiana Uni
 versity in 1938\, where they were installed in three locations on the Blo
 omington campus.&#160\;</p><h4><strong>About Your Guide:</strong></h4><p>
   Jim Davis is a Senior Lecturer in the Kelley School of Business\, in th
 e department of Management and Entrepreneurship. He has been serving as a
  docent and museum guide at the IU Eskenazi Museum of Art for the past te
 n years.&#160\; &#160\; &#160\;</p><h4><strong><span data-contrast="auto"
