LOCATION:SIDNEY AND LOIS ESKENAZI MUSEUM OF ART
GEO:39.169144;-86.519739
SUMMARY:Homeschool Day: America 250
DESCRIPTION:Travel back in time with us to America in 1776 to meet George
  Washington and see the Declaration of Independence up close. Together\, 
 we'll explore the art and stories that shaped our nation's founding. Afte
 rwards\, we'll create our own colonial-inspired artwork in the studio\, r
 eflecting on the theme of "What America Means to Me."Know Before You Go: 
  Meet us on the 1st floor of the museum at 10 a.m. Together\, we'll drop 
 off personal items in the Simpson Center for Education before exploring t
 he galleries. After seeing artworks that will inspire our project\, we'll
  head back to the Roehm Family Art-Making Studio to create our own master
 pieces! Don't forget to dress for a mess!  Strollers are welcome. Chapero
 nes required. We ask that chaperones be 18 or older\, with one adult for 
 every 6 children.Parking Information:  The museum is in the pedestrian di
 strict of campus with several parking options nearby. The Indiana Memoria
 l Union lot (900 E. 7th Street) is just a 5-minute walk diagonal to the m
 useum\, and visitors can receive 40% off parking validation at the museum
 's guest services desk. The East Garage (105 N. Eagleson Ave.) and Fee La
 ne Garage (709 N. Fee Lane) are also convenient\, about an 8ŌĆō10 minute 
 walk. Learn more about parking on the Bloomington campus here (https://pa
 rking.indiana.edu/facilities/index.html).
