 ith Guest Services on the first floor
SUMMARY:Beginner/Intermediate Drawing Workshop
DESCRIPTION:Reserve your spot. If this page says\, "Registration has clos
 ed" that means the waitlist is full.SuppliesBring your favorite drawing p
 encil (e.g. 4B)\, a sketchbook or drawing paper\, and a phone or device t
 o photograph artwork (without flash) as we sketch.  Know Before You GoArr
 ive early to find parking\, check in\, and get your drawing supplies read
 y.  At 1:55 p.m. any unclaimed reservations will be released to guests wh
 o are standing by waiting for a spot.  Where to find us\, where to park\,
  accessibility\, and museum guidelines (https://artmuseum.indiana.edu/vis
 it/your-visit.html).  This workshop is recommended for ages 12 and up. An
 yone under 18\, who is not an IU student\, must be accompanied by an adul
 t.  When You ArriveCheck in with Guest Services at the information desk o
 n the first floor\, even if you come often and even if you are late. We a
 ppreciate having an accurate attendance count.  Store all backpacks and l
 arge bags before entering the galleries. A small handbag may be carried a
 t your side.  Get your supplies ready. Attach an 18x24" piece of newsprin
 t to a drawing board.  Cancellations  This workshop often has a waitlist.
  Please use the cancellation link included with your confirmation email i
 f your plans change.About the Instructor  John Cheek has taught credit an
 d non-credit classes for eight years in portrait painting\, landscape pai
 nting\, palette knife painting\, life drawing\, beginning drawing\, and a
 dvanced drawing\, as well as in design. He volunteers his time and expert
 ise to facilitate drawing workshops at the Eskenazi Museum of Art.
